In a speech delivered at the Davos Congress Centre in Switzerland, President Trump highlighted the economic success of the United States since his election, including the creation of over 7 million new jobs, the lowest unemployment rate in over 50 years, and record-low unemployment rates for African Americans, Hispanic Americans, Asian Americans, and women. He also mentioned the success of the U.S. stock markets, the new trade deal with China, and the upcoming negotiations with the World Trade Organization. President Trump expressed his desire for reform within the WTO and discussed the possibility of adding more countries to the travel ban. He also addressed the ongoing impeachment trial, expressing his belief that it is a hoax and criticizing the media and certain politicians.